---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Social Proof for Immigration Attorneys — Collect & Display Client Testimonials | SocialProof.dev">
  <main class="for-page">
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="badge">For Immigration Attorneys</div>
        <h1>The most referred attorneys are the most trusted. Make that trust visible.</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">Immigration clients choose their attorney based on who their community recommends. SocialProof helps you capture those recommendations and make them visible to every new prospect who visits your website.</p>
        <a href="https://app.socialproof.dev/register" class="btn-primary">Start free — no credit card</a>
        <p class="micro">Free forever for 1 active widget</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="problem">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Your best clients want to help others find you. Make it easy for them.</h2>
        <p>Immigration law is intensely personal. Families trust you with the most important legal matter of their lives — visa applications, green cards, citizenship, deportation defense. When you succeed, they're profoundly grateful.</p>
        <p>That gratitude drives referrals. But it rarely shows up on your website, where every new prospective client is trying to decide whether to trust you with their family's future.</p>
        <p>A single testimonial — "She guided my family through our green card application and was responsive every step of the way" — does more to build trust than any credential or bio.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="benefits">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Client testimonials built for a trust-first practice</h2>
        <div class="benefits-grid">
          <div class="benefit">
            <h3>🔒 Privacy-first collection</h3>
            <p>Immigration clients may be cautious about sharing publicly. You control every testimonial — approve, request edits, or simply don't publish. Full privacy is always in your hands.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="benefit">
            <h3>🌍 Multilingual-friendly</h3>
            <p>Your collection form accepts text in any language. Clients can write in Spanish, Mandarin, French, Portuguese — whatever is most natural for them.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="benefit">
            <h3>📱 Zero friction — works on any device</h3>
            <p>Your clients are often non-native English speakers navigating complex technology. Your collection link works on any phone, no app, no account needed.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="benefit">
            <h3>✅ Full review before publishing</h3>
            <p>Every submission is held in your dashboard until you approve it. Nothing goes live that you haven't vetted.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="benefit">
            <h3>🖥️ Embeds on any website</h3>
            <p>WordPress, Squarespace, or any HTML site — one script tag and your testimonials widget is live on your practice website.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="benefit">
            <h3>🔗 Case-type organization</h3>
            <p>Create separate collection campaigns for family immigration, employment visas, asylum cases — then display the right testimonials on each relevant service page.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="sample-widget">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>The kind of trust signal that converts inquiries into clients</h2>
        <div class="widget-preview">
          <blockquote>
            <p>"Attorney Chen helped our family navigate the I-485 process when we felt completely lost. She was patient, thorough, and returned every email within hours. We got our green cards approved — we can't thank her enough or recommend her strongly enough."</p>
            <footer>— Wei and Mei L., San Francisco CA · ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐</footer>
          </blockquote>
        </div>
        <p>This is what a new client sees before they decide whether to call you for a consultation.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="how-it-works">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Add to your practice in 15 minutes</h2>
        <ol class="steps">
          <li><strong>Create your free account</strong> at app.socialproof.dev</li>
          <li><strong>Get your collection link</strong></li>
          <li><strong>Include it in your case-closure email</strong> — when the result is positive</li>
          <li><strong>Review and approve</strong> testimonials in your dashboard</li>
          <li><strong>Embed the widget</strong> on your practice's website or consultation booking page</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="faq">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Questions from immigration attorneys</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>My clients are private. Will they be comfortable with this?</h3>
            <p>You control everything. You can publish just a first name and city, initials only, or "Anonymous" — whatever the client is comfortable with. You can confirm with each client before publishing. Nothing goes live without your approval.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Are there bar association rules about client testimonials?</h3>
            <p>Bar rules vary by state. We recommend consulting your state bar's advertising rules. Generally, testimonials from actual clients about their experience (not promises of results) are permitted with appropriate disclosures. We're not legal advisors — please verify with your bar association.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Can clients write in languages other than English?</h3>
            <p>Absolutely. The form accepts any text. You can choose to display testimonials in their original language or request an English version from the client.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>How many testimonials can I collect on the free plan?</h3>
            <p>Unlimited testimonial submissions, unlimited approvals. The free plan includes 1 active widget. Pro ($9/mo) gives you unlimited widgets and removes SocialProof branding.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="cta">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Turn your client success stories into your strongest marketing asset</h2>
        <p>Free forever for 1 active widget. Set up in minutes.</p>
        <a href="https://app.socialproof.dev/register" class="btn-primary">Start free today</a>
        <p class="micro">Free forever for 1 active widget · No credit card required</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

<div class="footer-links" style="margin-top:2rem;padding-top:1.5rem;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:0.9rem;">
  <strong style="color:#374151;">Also explore:</strong>
  <a href="/for/coaches" style="display:inline-block;margin:0.3rem 0.5rem 0.3rem 0;color:#2563eb;text-decoration:none;">For Coaches</a>
  <a href="/for/freelancers" style="display:inline-block;margin:0.3rem 0.5rem 0.3rem 0;color:#2563eb;text-decoration:none;">For Freelancers</a>
  <a href="/for/restaurants" style="display:inline-block;margin:0.3rem 0.5rem 0.3rem 0;color:#2563eb;text-decoration:none;">For Restaurants</a>
  <a href="/vs/senja" style="display:inline-block;margin:0.3rem 0.5rem 0.3rem 0;color:#2563eb;text-decoration:none;">vs Senja</a>
  <a href="/vs/testimonial" style="display:inline-block;margin:0.3rem 0.5rem 0.3rem 0;color:#2563eb;text-decoration:none;">vs Testimonial.to</a>
</div>
</Base>
